#: 21337012-0-1427
msgctxt "21337012-0-1427"
msgid "—transcribed from the oral tradition by an unknown author—"
"\n"
"\nSing, Valenwood, shout Green"
"\nTell the tale of the mover, the shaper, "
"\nthe one, the Wilderking."
"\n"
"\nHis eye projects outward to the world"
"\nand touches everything he perceives:"
"\nby his thoughts he shapes it."
"\n"
"\nDo you know where to find him?"
"\nHave you looked to the hills?"
"\nHave you looked to the trees?"
"\n"
"\nHe is not there."
"\nBecause "there" is a place, and a place has boundaries,"
"\nbut The Wilderking is boundless."
"\n"
"\nHis is the Court and the Throne."
"\nHe is the Court and the Throne."
"\nWhen he walks, his footfalls fall on himself."
"\n"
"\nAnd who does not hear his footfalls and quake?"
"\nThe earth shakes at his coming,"
"\nat the rising of his Hollow from the earth."
"\n"
"\nLike the delicate calm of an undisturbed pool"
"\nis shattered by the smallest of stones,"
"\nso is the terrible force of the Wilderking's passing."
"\n"
"\nShout, Bramblebreach! Wail, Shadows Watch!"
"\nThe Wilderking is friend and foe,"
"\nFoe and friend to both."
"\n"
"\nFor who can record his footsteps on the land,"
"\nwho can hear the melody of his voice,"
"\nwhen he opens his mouth to sing?"
msgstr "――作者不詳の口承文学を聞き書きしたもの――\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n歌え、ヴァレンウッド。叫べ、「緑」よ\\r"
"\n動く者、形を与える者の物語を語れ\\r"
"\nその名はさまよえる王\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n彼の目は世界に向かって突き出し\\r"
"\n知覚するもの全てに触れる\\r"
"\n彼は思考によって、形を与える\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n果たして彼はどこにいるのか\\r"
"\n山だろうか\\r"
"\n森だろうか\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n否。そこに彼はいない\\r"
"\nなぜなら、「そこ」とは場所であり、場所には際限がある\\r"
"\nさまよえる王に際限はない\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n彼は宮廷にして玉座\\r"
"\n彼は宮廷にして玉座\\r"
"\n彼が歩めば、踏み出した足は自身の上に落ちる\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n彼の足音と地響きを、誰が聞かずにいられるだろう？\\r"
"\n彼の到来とともに大地は震える\\r"
"\n地下から彼のホロウがせりあがる\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\nさざ波一つない水面の儚い静けさが\\r"
"\n極小の石つぶてで粉々に砕けるごとく\\r"
"\nさまよえる王が通り過ぎる時、恐るべき力が伝わる\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n叫べ、ブランブルブリーチよ！ むせび泣くがいい、影の守人よ！\\r"
"\nさまよえる王は味方にして敵\\r"
"\n敵にして味方なり\\r"
"\n\\r"
"\n彼の足音を、誰が記録にとどめられるだろう？\\r"
"\n彼が口を開いて歌う時\\r"
"\n誰がその旋律を耳にできるだろう？"

